01:13:03,000 --> 01:13:07,000
The Stampede counts as a slam so I can double that for even more craziness

274
01:13:09,000 --> 01:13:13,000
If you want to go a little faster and be a little more defensive, equip a shield

275
01:13:13,000 --> 01:13:19,000
In P.O.E. 2 you can raise your shield at any time to block all damage from the front, even spells

276
01:13:19,000 --> 01:13:23,000
While holding up your shield your stun meter will build as you take damage, so be careful

277
01:13:23,000 --> 01:13:27,000
If it reaches 100% your stance will break and you will be vulnerable

278
01:13:28,000 --> 01:13:33,000
Some enemies also have unblockable attacks which are indicated by this red flash

279
01:13:33,000 --> 01:13:36,000
If you see one of these coming, make sure to dodge out of the way

280
01:13:38,000 --> 01:13:42,000
Using a shield also gives you access to shield skills like Shield Charge

281
01:13:42,000 --> 01:13:45,000
which allows you to charge towards enemies and stun them

282
01:13:45,000 --> 01:13:50,000
While charging you're also blocking the whole time so you have full damage immunity from the front

283
01:13:51,000 --> 01:13:54,000
The Warrior also has access to totems

284
01:13:54,000 --> 01:13:57,000
Some totems have built-in abilities like Shockwave Totem

285
01:13:57,000 --> 01:14:01,000
which can be placed to stun nearby enemies and trigger aftershocks like those from the earthquake

286
01:14:01,000 --> 01:14:06,000
But you can also get Ancestral Warrior Totems which allow you to use any slam skill in your repertoire

287
01:14:06,000 --> 01:14:10,000
This is a meta skill, which means that it's a skill you can put other skills into

288
01:14:10,000 --> 01:14:14,000
I can take a slam like Sunder and socket it into my Ancestral Warrior Totem

289
01:14:14,000 --> 01:14:18,000
Now when I summon him, he'll sit there and slam the monsters from a distance

290
01:14:19,000 --> 01:14:23,000
There are 20 active skills for Maces, so there's a lot more to try out

291
01:14:23,000 --> 01:14:27,000
But by endgame you're going to be dropping hammers from the sky, leaping fearlessly into combat

292
01:14:27,000 --> 01:14:30,000
and separating the very earth you stand on

293
01:14:33,000 --> 01:14:35,000
Time for some ranged attacks

294
01:14:35,000 --> 01:14:40,000
The Ranger is primarily about the bow, but we wanted to make sure that she feels agile as well

295
01:14:40,000 --> 01:14:43,000
In Pier 2 you can shoot while moving

296
01:14:43,000 --> 01:14:46,000
Combined with all the skills the Ranger has that allow you to jump around

297
01:14:46,000 --> 01:14:49,000
you'll have a lot of mobility in combat

298
01:14:51,000 --> 01:14:55,000
Bow skills have a variety of lightning, poison, ice and physical attacks

299
01:14:55,000 --> 01:14:58,000
Lightning attacks bounce around between targets

300
01:14:58,000 --> 01:15:02,000
You can also stick lightning arrows in the ground which explode when hit by the bounces

301
01:15:02,000 --> 01:15:05,000
or electrocute enemies to take them out of combat

302
01:15:07,000 --> 01:15:11,000
Ice attacks later slow and freeze enemies to keep them away from you

303
01:15:12,000 --> 01:15:15,000
Using poison not only can you slowly damage your enemies from afar

304
01:15:15,000 --> 01:15:18,000
but also grow some interesting plants

305
01:15:20,000 --> 01:15:24,000
With 21 bow skills and all the mobility and combo tools the Ranger has

306
01:15:24,000 --> 01:15:26,000
you can take advantage of every situation

307
01:15:26,000 --> 01:15:28,000
By endgame you'll be creating hundreds of arrows

308
01:15:28,000 --> 01:15:33,000
be they falling from the sky, bouncing around between enemies or spraying out of tornadoes

309
01:15:34,000 --> 01:15:38,000
You might have noticed in the bottom left of the screen that the flask slots look a little different

310
01:15:38,000 --> 01:15:43,000
In Pier 2 you have one dedicated life flask slot and one mana flask slot

311
01:15:43,000 --> 01:15:46,000
Flasks gain charges as you kill enemies

312
01:15:46,000 --> 01:15:49,000
and typically allow you to heal 6 or 7 times if they're full

313
01:15:50,000 --> 01:15:53,000
But that's not the only thing you can use charges for

314
01:15:53,000 --> 01:15:58,000
Charms are a new item type that will automatically defend you from various debuffs or damage types

315
01:15:58,000 --> 01:16:00,000
Having trouble with getting frozen?

316
01:16:00,000 --> 01:16:02,000
Equip a thawing charm

317
01:16:02,000 --> 01:16:07,000
When it's fully charged it will make you immune to freeze for 3 seconds if you get frozen

318
01:16:07,000 --> 01:16:10,000
To recharge them just kill more monsters

319
01:16:11,000 --> 01:16:14,000
You can gain more slots for charms by upgrading your belt

320
01:16:17,000 --> 01:16:20,000
The Mercenary wields a crossbow that can be loaded with different ammo types

321
01:16:20,000 --> 01:16:23,000
offering versatility, power and mobility

322
01:16:23,000 --> 01:16:27,000
All classes in Path of Exile 2 can be controlled with WASD

323
01:16:27,000 --> 01:16:29,000
which makes this class play exactly like a shooter

324
01:16:29,000 --> 01:16:32,000
For the crossbow you will find skills that work like shotguns

325
01:16:32,000 --> 01:16:34,000
sniper rifles

326
01:16:34,000 --> 01:16:35,000
assault rifles

327
01:16:35,000 --> 01:16:37,000
and even grenade launchers

328
01:16:37,000 --> 01:16:41,000
But not only that there are a wide variety of more interesting elemental ammos too

329
01:16:41,000 --> 01:16:45,000
It's very fast to switch between ammo types as long as you already have them loaded

330
01:16:45,000 --> 01:16:49,000
which makes the Mercenary able to combo abilities together for devastating effect

331
01:16:51,000 --> 01:16:55,000
Use Glacial Bolt to create walls of ice to separate enemies

332
01:16:55,000 --> 01:16:59,000
then switch to Fragmentation Rounds to explode the ice dealing massive AOE damage

333
01:16:59,000 --> 01:17:04,000
If I come across an armoured enemy I could use Armour-Piercing Rounds to break their armour

334
01:17:04,000 --> 01:17:06,000
and then High Velocity Rounds to take them down

335
01:17:06,000 --> 01:17:09,000
Or perhaps I could fire a Gas Grenade to poison enemies

336
01:17:09,000 --> 01:17:12,000
before detonating the cloud with an Explosive Shot for massive damage

337
01:17:15,000 --> 01:17:19,000
If you want to call in some suppressing fire you can summon Artillery Ballistas

338
01:17:19,000 --> 01:17:24,000
These have a minimum range so you'll want to prepare your position carefully before moving in

339
01:17:26,000 --> 01:17:29,000
There are 22 active skills for crossbows

340
01:17:29,000 --> 01:17:32,000
By endgame you'll be calling Destruction down from the sky

341
01:17:32,000 --> 01:17:36,000
as you litter the battlefield with grenades and pepper your enemies with your automatic shotgun

342
01:17:37,000 --> 01:17:40,000
If you're looking to take a backseat and let your minions do the work

343
01:17:40,000 --> 01:17:42,000
then the witch should be your choice

344
01:17:42,000 --> 01:17:45,000
She can call forth hordes of undead monsters to fight for her

345
01:17:45,000 --> 01:17:48,000
while casting powerful Chaos spells that debilitate her enemies

346
01:17:49,000 --> 01:17:52,000
Occult skills are some of the most varied in the game

347
01:17:52,000 --> 01:17:56,000
with skeletons, noxious spells, specialty minions, curses and sacrificial magic

348
01:17:57,000 --> 01:18:01,000
Before we talk about minions we'll have to talk about a new resource in Path of Exile 2 called Spirit

349
01:18:01,000 --> 01:18:05,000
This is a Spirit Gem which allows you to pick from a range of persistent skills

350
01:18:06,000 --> 01:18:10,000
All classes have a variety of these skills which can add some very interesting effects

351
01:18:10,000 --> 01:18:13,000
like Arctic Armor which does cold damage to enemies that hit you

352
01:18:13,000 --> 01:18:17,000
or Raging Spirits which summon fiery skulls each time you cast a fire spell

353
01:18:18,000 --> 01:18:22,000
For the witch though we'll want to be using our spirit to create permanent minions

354
01:18:22,000 --> 01:18:25,000
These minions will be revived automatically when they die

355
01:18:25,000 --> 01:18:27,000
so you don't have to worry about resummoning them all the time

356
01:18:27,000 --> 01:18:31,000
Here I'm using the skill screen to allocate which minions I would like in my horde

357
01:18:31,000 --> 01:18:34,000
You can see the spirit cost of each one

358
01:18:34,000 --> 01:18:39,000
Skeletal warriors are cheap but weak, useful for tanking damage and distracting enemies

359
01:18:39,000 --> 01:18:41,000
But I want more heavy hitters in my army

360
01:18:41,000 --> 01:18:45,000
so I'm going to unsummon some warriors and instead add skeletal arsonists

361
01:18:46,000 --> 01:18:50,000
Permanent minions come with special active abilities called command skills

362
01:18:50,000 --> 01:18:54,000
You can order these guys to detonate your own minions for even more damage and area of effect

363
01:18:54,000 --> 01:18:56,000
If you want a bigger army you'll need a scepter

364
01:18:56,000 --> 01:19:01,000
This new weapon type is imbued with even more spirit allowing you to summon even more friends

365
01:19:01,000 --> 01:19:07,000
And if you want an even bigger army than that you can take advantage of corpses to summon true hordes of minions

366
01:19:07,000 --> 01:19:10,000
But what can a witch do while her army is at work?

367
01:19:10,000 --> 01:19:15,000
Well she has a range of chaos spells to spread disease amongst your enemies or bone skills to impale them

368
01:19:15,000 --> 01:19:19,000
Or you know, you could curse them to make them weaker so your horde can take them down

369
01:19:19,000 --> 01:19:21,000
There are 25 active occult skills

370
01:19:21,000 --> 01:19:26,000
By the endgame you'll be the leader of a fearsome army of the dead consuming everything in its path

371
01:19:28,000 --> 01:19:33,000
The sorceress bends the elements to her will using them to unleash devastation on her foes

372
01:19:33,000 --> 01:19:37,000
This classic spellcaster weaves a flurry of elemental magic from afar

373
01:19:38,000 --> 01:19:41,000
The elemental skills have everything you might expect and more

374
01:19:41,000 --> 01:19:44,000
Fireballs, icy explosions, lightning, and fireballs

375
01:19:44,000 --> 01:19:47,000
The elemental skills have everything you might expect and more

376
01:19:47,000 --> 01:19:51,000
Fireballs, icy explosions, lightning storms, you get the idea

377
01:19:51,000 --> 01:19:56,000
Each spell is unique and has many different ways to build and combo with others, even between different elements

378
01:19:56,000 --> 01:20:04,000
For example, flame wall conjures a burning line that not only damages enemies but also empowers all projectiles that pass through it

379
01:20:04,000 --> 01:20:08,000
If you place a wall and fire lightning sparks through it, they'll gain extra fire damage

380
01:20:09,000 --> 01:20:13,000
It's a good idea to take advantage of the ability to automatically swap weapons when you use certain skills

381
01:20:13,000 --> 01:20:20,000
Having a special staff with bonuses to fire skills and another with bonuses to lightning skills can really power up a combo like this

382
01:20:20,000 --> 01:20:24,000
The sorceress can also take advantage of powerful trigger gems

383
01:20:24,000 --> 01:20:28,000
For example, you could grab the cast and ignite gem and use it with firestorm

384
01:20:28,000 --> 01:20:32,000
As you ignite enemies, a counter will go up in the top left corner

385
01:20:32,000 --> 01:20:36,000
When it's full, a firestorm will automatically be cast to the enemy that was ignited

386
01:20:37,000 --> 01:20:40,000
There are 25 active elemental skills

387
01:20:40,000 --> 01:20:45,000
By endgame, you'll be firing off projectiles left and right as you rain down elemental storms on your foes

388
01:20:46,000 --> 01:20:49,000
Now, those are the characters that will be available at the start of early access

389
01:20:49,000 --> 01:20:54,000
But we will be adding 6 more character classes with just as many skills and options as these

390
01:20:54,000 --> 01:20:56,000
There's a lot more to come

391
01:20:57,000 --> 01:20:59,000
There's one more important thing to mention about skills

392
01:20:59,000 --> 01:21:04,000
Even though we talk about them as belonging to each class, in reality there are no restrictions

393
01:21:04,000 --> 01:21:08,000
You can use all these skills on any class so long as you have the attributes

394
01:21:08,000 --> 01:21:14,000
For example, a poison ranger might want to try out using occult curses to increase her poison damage

395
01:21:14,000 --> 01:21:19,000
Or a monk might want to trigger elemental ice walls to use with his glacial cascade combo

396
01:21:19,000 --> 01:21:22,000
The possibilities for cross-class combos are practically unlimited

397
01:21:22,000 --> 01:21:25,000
We're looking forward to what kind of things you guys might find

398
01:21:25,000 --> 01:21:29,000
Now, Path of Exile is a game known for build customization

399
01:21:29,000 --> 01:21:32,000
And we haven't even scratched the surface of what is possible yet

400
01:21:33,000 --> 01:21:35,000
So let's talk about support gems

401
01:21:35,000 --> 01:21:42,000
Path of Exile 2 has a system of support gems that can be combined with your active skills to dramatically change the way they work

402
01:21:42,000 --> 01:21:46,000
If you find a support gem, then right-clicking it will open up this screen

403
01:21:46,000 --> 01:21:51,000
Here you will find a variety of recommended support gems for each of your skills that you can pick between

404
01:21:51,000 --> 01:21:57,000
For example, this is a multiple projectile support gem and can be used to add multiple projectiles to any skill

405
01:21:57,000 --> 01:22:01,000
Normally when you fire a grenade, it will look like this

406
01:22:01,000 --> 01:22:04,000
But if we add multiple projectiles, then you get three of them

407
01:22:04,000 --> 01:22:09,000
Once you have the gem, you can also freely move it between any of the skills on your character

408
01:22:09,000 --> 01:22:15,000
If you want to have a multi-shot sniper rifle instead, then simply move the gem over to your high-velocity round skill

409
01:22:15,000 --> 01:22:22,000
Generally speaking, if it sounds like a support gem should work with a skill, then it will work, so it's a good idea to experiment

410
01:22:22,000 --> 01:22:25,000
Note that you can only have one of each support gem on your character

411
01:22:25,000 --> 01:22:33,000
Note that you can only have one of each support gem on your character, so you'll want to think carefully about which supports can be used best with each skill for maximum damage

412
01:22:33,000 --> 01:22:37,000
Now, if you want to stick to the recommendations, you should have a perfectly good time

413
01:22:37,000 --> 01:22:44,000
But if you want to experiment a bit more, then uncheck that recommended button and you can see the full list of supports that will work with your skill

414
01:22:44,000 --> 01:22:50,000
There are hundreds of support gems to choose from, and even we don't know the results of all the possible ways these can interact

415
01:22:50,000 --> 01:22:56,000
Each skill can have up to five supports socketed into it, and if you're clever, you can come up with some pretty interesting ideas

416
01:22:56,000 --> 01:22:59,000
Now, all of this is just scratching the surface

417
01:22:59,000 --> 01:23:04,000
You can make frost vortexes, break people's armor, make minions explode, make skills repeat

418
01:23:04,000 --> 01:23:09,000
Make enemies set each other on fire, cull enemies, or pin them to the ground

419
01:23:09,000 --> 01:23:17,000
Supports let you drastically change the behavior of your skills and create your own unique build, or at least follow someone's OP build guide

420
01:23:17,000 --> 01:23:23,000
So, speaking of builds, let's talk about one of the most iconic Path of Exile systems, the passive skill tree

421
01:23:23,000 --> 01:23:28,000
Yes, it's huge. There are over 1,500 nodes on there

422
01:23:28,000 --> 01:23:33,000
Now, a lot of people open the tree and can get a little intimidated at first, but try not to be scared

423
01:23:33,000 --> 01:23:37,000
There are lots of options, but at its core, it's pretty simple

424
01:23:37,000 --> 01:23:40,000
Each level, you get one point to put into the tree

425
01:23:40,000 --> 01:23:44,000
Each class starts at a different location, but they all share the same tree

426
01:23:44,000 --> 01:23:48,000
Around your section of the tree, you'll find relevant bonuses for your character

427
01:23:48,000 --> 01:23:51,000
You should be safe in the knowledge that there aren't many wrong choices here

428
01:23:51,000 --> 01:23:55,000
Almost all the starting nodes will be useful for your character in some way

429
01:23:55,000 --> 01:24:01,000
But if you do happen to make a choice you regret, you'll be able to re-spec any nodes you've taken by spending a little bit of gold

430
01:24:06,000 --> 01:24:10,000
Now, the tree is generally divided up into clusters which have similar themes

431
01:24:10,000 --> 01:24:17,000
In each cluster, you'll find small nodes that give simple bonuses like increased damage, but the real power comes from notables

432
01:24:17,000 --> 01:24:24,000
Notables normally have much more interesting bonuses, and they tend to care a lot more about how your build works and what skills you're using

433
01:24:24,000 --> 01:24:31,000
For example, in the mercenary area of the tree, this one gives a 25% chance for crossbow skills to not consume a bolt

434
01:24:31,000 --> 01:24:36,000
And here's one that gives grenades a chance to blow up a second time

435
01:24:37,000 --> 01:24:44,000
This one gives a chance for projectiles to rebound off terrain, as well as giving you some pierce chance to make that more likely

436
01:24:44,000 --> 01:24:53,000
Note that even though this is in the mercenary section, this would work with projectiles from all classes, so there are often reasons to go to different areas of the tree

437
01:24:53,000 --> 01:24:59,000
In order to get between these clusters, you will generally have to allocate nodes in the attribute highways

438
01:24:59,000 --> 01:25:06,000
Attribute nodes allow you to pick which attribute you would like to use, so it's very easy to get points for any attribute that your gear might need

439
01:25:06,000 --> 01:25:11,000
You can change which attribute these nodes give you for half price at the respec vendor

440
01:25:11,000 --> 01:25:16,000
In addition to notables, you will also find even larger passives called keystones

441
01:25:16,000 --> 01:25:22,000
Keystones have both an upside and a downside, and often require changing your entire build to design around them

442
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:30,000
A great example is Giant's Blood, which allows you to wield two-hand weapons in a single hand, but doubles the attribute requirements of them

443
01:25:30,000 --> 01:25:35,000
You can use a two-hand mace with a shield, or even dual wield them

444
01:25:38,000 --> 01:25:45,000
Or how about Mind Over Matter, which makes all damage go to your mana pool first before your life pool, but you lose 50% of your mana regen

445
01:25:45,000 --> 01:25:51,000
Skills like these can be tough to build around, but if you're up for the challenge, they can be very rewarding

446
01:25:52,000 --> 01:25:58,000
As we showed you earlier on the Sorceress, you can swap between weapon sets on the fly as you use certain skills

447
01:25:58,000 --> 01:26:08,000
One of the new features in Path of Exile 2's passive tree is that you can choose to have your passive tree change as you switch between weapon sets to take advantage of specific bonuses on the tree

448
01:26:08,000 --> 01:26:13,000
For the Sorceress, you might want to change between fire and lightning specialization

449
01:26:14,000 --> 01:26:21,000
Or you could switch between one-hand and a two-hand setup in order to be able to block boss attacks while following up with heavy hits from your bigger mace

450
01:26:22,000 --> 01:26:29,000
Or perhaps you could have a full curse setup on your witch to debuff enemies before switching to a Chaos Degen build for maximum damage

451
01:26:31,000 --> 01:26:38,000
If you want to stick with just one weapon set, you can just use these specialization points as bonus points to invest however you like

452
01:26:38,000 --> 01:26:42,000
But creative players will find plenty of opportunities with this system

453
01:26:42,000 --> 01:26:48,000
You can get weapon specialization points throughout the campaign from optional bosses and quests

454
01:26:48,000 --> 01:26:52,000
For example, if I manage to defeat the Crowbell, I'll get a weapon specialization book

455
01:26:53,000 --> 01:26:57,000
There are lots of other permanent boosts available from the campaign too

456
01:26:57,000 --> 01:27:01,000
On the map you can see icons that indicate the many optional encounters you can find

457
01:27:01,000 --> 01:27:05,000
Some of them have permanent character boosts and others have powerful items

458
01:27:05,000 --> 01:27:10,000
If you're having trouble getting past a boss, it might be a good idea to explore and see what you can find

459
01:27:10,000 --> 01:27:15,000
For example, if you defeat Blackjaw the Remnant, you'll gain a permanent increase to fire resistance

460
01:27:16,000 --> 01:27:19,000
One of the most important finds are Spirit bonuses

461
01:27:19,000 --> 01:27:22,000
You can find the first one here in the canopy in Act 1

462
01:27:22,000 --> 01:27:26,000
Defeat the boss in this area to acquire a permanent addition of Spirit

463
01:27:26,000 --> 01:27:31,000
The permanent buffs you gain from Spirit are very powerful and every class will find a use for them

464
01:27:31,000 --> 01:27:35,000
So make sure you hunt down these upgrades. There's one in each Act

465
01:27:35,000 --> 01:27:39,000
Now we haven't even talked about the most important element of character progression, items

466
01:27:39,000 --> 01:27:41,000
That's why we're all here, right?

467
01:27:41,000 --> 01:27:45,000
Items in Path of Exile can be broken down into four rarity groups

468
01:27:45,000 --> 01:27:48,000
Normal, Magic, Rare and Unique

469
01:27:48,000 --> 01:27:53,000
One of the things you're going to want to do as you play through the campaign is upgrade the items you find

470
01:27:53,000 --> 01:27:55,000
And you can do that with currency items

471
01:27:55,000 --> 01:28:00,000
An Orb of Transmutation will allow you to upgrade a normal item to a magic item with one mod

472
01:28:00,000 --> 01:28:04,000
You can then apply an Orb of Augmentation to add a second mod

473
01:28:04,000 --> 01:28:08,000
Then use a Regal Orb to add a third mod and upgrade it to a rare

474
01:28:08,000 --> 01:28:13,000
Finally, you can use some Exalted Orbs to add more mods to your rare to a total of six mods

475
01:28:15,000 --> 01:28:20,000
One of the things we think is really important is to make these options available to use as you play

476
01:28:20,000 --> 01:28:24,000
All the items that add mods are much more common than they were in Path of Exile 1

477
01:28:24,000 --> 01:28:27,000
So that you can use them throughout your campaign playthrough

478
01:28:27,000 --> 01:28:32,000
We want you to find things on the ground that can be crafted into upgrades much more frequently

479
01:28:32,000 --> 01:28:35,000
As well as making the drop rates on these items much more common

480
01:28:35,000 --> 01:28:39,000
You can also get them by disenchanting unwanted gear at the magic item vendor

481
01:28:39,000 --> 01:28:43,000
If you disenchant magic items you can build up to an Orb of Transmutation

482
01:28:43,000 --> 01:28:46,000
And by disenchanting rares you can build up to Regal Orbs

483
01:28:47,000 --> 01:28:51,000
Another important area of crafting items in POE 2 is sockets

484
01:28:51,000 --> 01:28:56,000
Some items you find will have sockets that can have Esamite runes placed in them that add more mods to the item

485
01:28:56,000 --> 01:29:01,000
If I insert this Glacial Rune into my helmet it will give extra cold resistance

486
01:29:01,000 --> 01:29:05,000
This is a great way to solve problems that you have with your build like resistances or damage

487
01:29:05,000 --> 01:29:08,000
If you find socketed items that you don't have a use for

488
01:29:08,000 --> 01:29:12,000
You can take them to the salvage bench in town to work towards an Artifices Orb

489
01:29:12,000 --> 01:29:15,000
This will allow you to add sockets to your existing items

490
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:18,000
Body armors and two-hand weapons can have up to two sockets

491
01:29:18,000 --> 01:29:22,000
While the rest of your armor and one-hand weapons can only have one socket

492
01:29:22,000 --> 01:29:27,000
You can also salvage items with quality to create items like armor scraps or whetstones

493
01:29:27,000 --> 01:29:31,000
These will allow you to increase the quality of your items for an up to 20% boost

494
01:29:32,000 --> 01:29:36,000
If you don't want to disenchant or salvage your items you can always sell them for gold

495
01:29:36,000 --> 01:29:43,000
Gold can be used to buy items from vendors and we've tried to do a lot to make sure that the items they have for sale are actually useful

496
01:29:43,000 --> 01:29:47,000
Every time you level up they get more stock so make sure to check back often

497
01:29:47,000 --> 01:29:49,000
Other vendors offer a gamble

498
01:29:49,000 --> 01:29:53,000
Pay a flat amount of gold and you'll get a random item of a specific type

499
01:29:53,000 --> 01:29:56,000
This could be a great way to improve your gear if you're lucky

500
01:29:56,000 --> 01:29:59,000
Gold is also used to respec your passive skills

501
01:29:59,000 --> 01:30:03,000
Take advantage of this system to experiment with your tree and rework it as required

502
01:30:04,000 --> 01:30:07,000
The other thing you might want to use gold for is the currency exchange

503
01:30:07,000 --> 01:30:13,000
This allows you to exchange currency items with other players on an open market in exchange for a small gold fee

504
01:30:14,000 --> 01:30:17,000
Now all items in Path of Exile are freely tradable

505
01:30:17,000 --> 01:30:20,000
We never bind anything to your character except gold

506
01:30:20,000 --> 01:30:25,000
Now most gear in Path of Exile 2 is randomly generated but there's another type that isn't

507
01:30:25,000 --> 01:30:27,000
Uniques

508
01:30:27,000 --> 01:30:33,000
They are especially rare, each with a handcrafted set of unusual mods which can dramatically change a character's build

509
01:30:33,000 --> 01:30:38,000
They're not just better rare items, they can do much stranger things that can fundamentally change your character

510
01:30:39,000 --> 01:30:44,000
Corpse Wade will make any corpses you run through explode into clouds of poison

511
01:30:44,000 --> 01:30:51,000
The Sands of Silk is a body armor that changes your dodge roll into a blink, morphing you into sand as you teleport past your foes

512
01:30:51,000 --> 01:30:58,000
And of course some uniques are just pure hits of dopamine, like Quill Reign, which just turns your bow attacks into full auto by doubling your attack speed

513
01:31:00,000 --> 01:31:03,000
Each unique is something that you can build your character around

514
01:31:03,000 --> 01:31:08,000
We try to make sure that most unique items have a potential use at endgame, even if you find them early on

515
01:31:08,000 --> 01:31:12,000
And as you can see, every unique item has a potential use at endgame, even if you find them early on

516
01:31:12,000 --> 01:31:16,000
And as you can see, every unique item has a potential use at endgame, even if you find them early on

517
01:31:19,000 --> 01:31:23,000
The last character progression system that you can do during the campaign is Ascension

518
01:31:23,000 --> 01:31:29,000
Starting in Act 2 you will come across Ascension trials, tests that you must complete to unlock your Ascension class

519
01:31:29,000 --> 01:31:34,000
We'll explain these trials soon, but first let's take a look at what Ascending can do for your character

520
01:31:34,000 --> 01:31:40,000
Each class has access to 3 Ascension classes, but at the start of early access only 2 per class will be available

521
01:31:41,000 --> 01:31:47,000
Ascension classes are unique to each character class, so choose wisely, they can drastically affect how you build your character

522
01:31:49,000 --> 01:31:53,000
As a sorceress you could become a Stormweaver, a master of the elements

523
01:31:53,000 --> 01:31:58,000
Tempest Caller causes elemental storms to be summoned each time you do a critical hit with a spell

524
01:32:00,000 --> 01:32:03,000
With Strike twice you can stack 2 copies of Shock for more damage

525
01:32:03,000 --> 01:32:07,000
And going deeper into the tree you can make all your damage types apply Shock

526
01:32:07,000 --> 01:32:09,000
Make a Shock build from any skill

527
01:32:10,000 --> 01:32:14,000
Alternatively you could become a Chrono-mancer and command Time itself

528
01:32:14,000 --> 01:32:18,000
She literally has the ability to stop time with Time Freeze

529
01:32:18,000 --> 01:32:21,000
Not only that, but she has many other time manipulation abilities

530
01:32:21,000 --> 01:32:28,000
Using Temporal Rift she can teleport back to a previous location, resetting her life and mana back to what it was

531
01:32:28,000 --> 01:32:32,000
Or with Time Snap she can reset all her cooldowns and cast all her spells again

532
01:32:33,000 --> 01:32:37,000
On the Warrior you can choose between the Warbringer or the Titan

533
01:32:37,000 --> 01:32:41,000
The Warbringer channels the might of his ancestors to gain tremendous power

534
01:32:41,000 --> 01:32:46,000
Using Answered Call you can summon ancestral spirits linked to each of your totems

535
01:32:46,000 --> 01:32:52,000
With Jade Heritage you can encase your body in a protective layer that absorbs all damage until it breaks

536
01:32:53,000 --> 01:32:57,000
Warcaller's Bellow allows you to explode the corpses of your enemies

537
01:32:57,000 --> 01:33:01,000
And with Great Wolf's Howl you can ignore the cooldowns of your Warcries

538
01:33:02,000 --> 01:33:04,000
Let all that anger out

539
01:33:05,000 --> 01:33:07,000
The Titan class is all about hitting big

540
01:33:08,000 --> 01:33:11,000
With Earthbreaker every slam is a chance to create an aftershock

541
01:33:13,000 --> 01:33:18,000
With Crushing Impacts every hit becomes a crushing blow which will allow you to stun your enemies with ease

542
01:33:19,000 --> 01:33:24,000
With Surprising Strength you can take advantage of stunned enemies to deal 40% more damage

543
01:33:27,000 --> 01:33:32,000
As a Ranger you might choose to be a Deadeye, an expert markswoman who can take down foes with style

544
01:33:33,000 --> 01:33:37,000
With Endless Munitions every attack gains an extra projectile

545
01:33:38,000 --> 01:33:45,000
With Gathering Winds she gains a small increase to movement speed with every attack, but be careful, she loses them when getting hit

546
01:33:46,000 --> 01:33:51,000
With Eagle Eyes she will never miss, allowing you to stop wasting all those passive points on accuracy

547
01:33:52,000 --> 01:33:56,000
Alternatively you could become a Pathfinder, the master of flasks and poison

548
01:33:57,000 --> 01:34:05,000
She can choose from one of several throwable concoctions, allowing her to spend her flask charges to throw explosive bottles that deal various types of damage

549
01:34:06,000 --> 01:34:12,000
A Bleeding concoction will make your enemies bleed, while a Fulminating one can shock your enemies, allowing you to do extra damage

550
01:34:13,000 --> 01:34:21,000
Contagious Contamination allows her to spread poisons between her foes, while Overwhelming Toxicity doubles the number of stacks they can be infected by

551
01:34:22,000 --> 01:34:29,000
Running Assault allows her to move much more quickly while firing, while Relentless Pursuit makes her totally immune to being slowed by enemies

552
01:34:31,000 --> 01:34:34,000
The Witch can ascend into the Infernalist or the Blood Mage

553
01:34:35,000 --> 01:34:38,000
As an Infernalist she can summon a loyal Hellhound companion

554
01:34:39,000 --> 01:34:44,000
The Hellhound sets enemies on fire, as well as taking a percentage of the damage if the Infernalist gets hit

555
01:34:45,000 --> 01:34:48,000
With Pyromantic Pact you can turn your mana into Infernal Flame

556
01:34:49,000 --> 01:34:53,000
As you cast more spells, the flame builds up and if it overflows you'll take damage

557
01:34:55,000 --> 01:34:58,000
Using Bringer of Flame you'll want to make sure you keep the flames topped up

558
01:34:59,000 --> 01:35:03,000
While your Infernal Flame is above 30% all damage from you and your minions will ignite enemies

559
01:35:05,000 --> 01:35:07,000
She can also transform into a literal Demon

560
01:35:08,000 --> 01:35:13,000
While in Demon form she takes an increasing amount of damage, but her cast speed and damage increase rapidly as well

561
01:35:14,000 --> 01:35:18,000
So if you're planning on transforming into a Demon, make sure you stack a lot of life recovery

562
01:35:20,000 --> 01:35:23,000
She can also become a Blood Mage, a master of life and energy

563
01:35:24,000 --> 01:35:28,000
All Blood Mages must pay the price of making skills cost life as well as mana

564
01:35:28,000 --> 01:35:33,000
But in exchange, every monster they kill will drop Life Remnants, which allow them to quickly gain back that life

565
01:35:35,000 --> 01:35:42,000
With Crimson Power she can gain large amounts of extra life, and with Vitality Siphon she can use her spells to leech life back as well

566
01:35:43,000 --> 01:35:48,000
Once you've got a significant amount of life, you can use Gore Spike to make your critical hits deal incredible amounts of damage

567
01:35:49,000 --> 01:35:52,000
A Monk who is in tune with the elements might become an Invoker

568
01:35:52,000 --> 01:35:58,000
With Elemental Expression the Invoker will create waves of elemental power each time he does a critical strike

569
01:35:59,000 --> 01:36:03,000
With Faith as a choice you gain the ability to meditate, allowing you to double your energy shield

570
01:36:04,000 --> 01:36:09,000
Choose between I Am the Blizzard or I Am the Thunder to specialize in cold or lightning

571
01:36:10,000 --> 01:36:13,000
And I Shall Rage will allow you to turn into an unbound avatar

572
01:36:14,000 --> 01:36:18,000
Each time you apply a status ailment to an enemy you gain unbound fury

573
01:36:18,000 --> 01:36:24,000
When you have enough, transform into an avatar to deal way more damage and inflict even more elemental ailments

574
01:36:25,000 --> 01:36:28,000
Some Monks choose to reach into the darkness instead

575
01:36:29,000 --> 01:36:36,000
The Acolyte of Chaiula can exchange their Mastery of Spirit for Darkness, a resource that can be utilized to both absorb and deal damage

576
01:36:37,000 --> 01:36:45,000
The Shroud of Darkness will protect you from all damage incoming, but if you take Grasp of the Void you will deal extra chaos damage from all the darkness you have

577
01:36:45,000 --> 01:36:55,000
Their Dark Pact offers greatly increased resistances to chaos damage and can allow their mana leech to not only happen instantly, but apply to their energy shield as well

578
01:36:56,000 --> 01:37:01,000
Another node you can take is Waking Dream, which allows you to see into the domain of the Breach Demons

579
01:37:02,000 --> 01:37:07,000
There you will see the Flames of Chaiula that can be taken to gain life, mana and damage

580
01:37:08,000 --> 01:37:14,000
The Mercenary has a job to do, but which job suits you? You might choose to become a Witch Hunter

581
01:37:15,000 --> 01:37:22,000
Obsessive Rituals will give you a Sorcery Ward, allowing you to defend yourself against elemental hits in exchange for less defense against attacks

582
01:37:23,000 --> 01:37:29,000
With Zealous Inquisition your enemies have a 10% chance to explode on death, the chance is doubled against Demons and Undead

583
01:37:30,000 --> 01:37:37,000
With Judge, Jury and Executioner, your initial hit against enemies can deal up to 30% of their life in damage, if you're lucky

584
01:37:38,000 --> 01:37:40,000
This is great for hunting powerful bosses

585
01:37:40,000 --> 01:37:46,000
And with Witch Bane, you can break your enemies concentration, preventing them from casting spells as often as they would usually do

586
01:37:47,000 --> 01:37:53,000
You could also choose to become a Gemling Legionnaire, enhancing your abilities by embedding gems directly in your flesh

587
01:37:54,000 --> 01:37:57,000
Integrated Efficiency will give you extra skill slots

588
01:37:58,000 --> 01:38:02,000
Thermatological Infusion gives you extra maximum resistances as you socket more and more support gems

589
01:38:03,000 --> 01:38:12,000
Adaptive Capability allows you to use any color of gem without worrying about attributes, while Crystalline Potential adds extra quality bonuses to every gem socketed into your character

590
01:38:13,000 --> 01:38:19,000
So those are the Ascenacy Classes for the start of Early Access, but one thing we haven't talked about yet is how you ascend in the first place

591
01:38:20,000 --> 01:38:27,000
Ascension in Path of Exile 2 requires completion of one of the Great Trials, which you'll find as you progress through the campaign

592
01:38:27,000 --> 01:38:31,000
Each one is associated with one of the major cultures of Rayclast

593
01:38:32,000 --> 01:38:41,000
Located in the Vastari Plains are the Mara'Keth, a culture of rich tales and brutal traditions who must do whatever it takes to survive in the desert

594
01:38:42,000 --> 01:38:47,000
The highest position in Mara'Keth culture is a Sekhema, and it is not a title given freely

595
01:38:48,000 --> 01:38:54,000
All aspirants must complete the Trial of the Sekhemas, a grueling gauntlet that will test their strength, will, cunning and patience

596
01:38:54,000 --> 01:39:01,000
To enter, a warrior of the Mara'Keth must prove their worth by trapping the soul of a djinn in a coin, and you are no different

597
01:39:04,000 --> 01:39:09,000
Once you have earned your coin, it may be placed in the Relic Altar to begin the Trial

598
01:39:15,000 --> 01:39:19,000
In the Trial of the Sekhemas, each room has its own challenges to overcome

599
01:39:19,000 --> 01:39:24,000
In this room, each rare monster you kill will send its blood to the chalice in the center of the room

600
01:39:25,000 --> 01:39:28,000
Once the chalice is filled, you will be able to proceed

601
01:39:29,000 --> 01:39:32,000
While fighting monsters in the Trial, you will need to be very careful

602
01:39:33,000 --> 01:39:35,000
Each hit will not only hurt you, but will damage your honor

603
01:39:36,000 --> 01:39:43,000
The monsters are well telegraphed, so that you can avoid their attacks, but if you run out of honor, you will fail the Trial and need to find another coin in order to try again

604
01:39:44,000 --> 01:39:48,000
It is a good idea to make sure that you are well prepared before challenging the Trial of the Sekhemas

605
01:39:50,000 --> 01:39:58,000
After each room, you will be rewarded. In this case, you have been given a key that can be used to unlock chests later in the Trial

606
01:39:59,000 --> 01:40:04,000
Once you have claimed your reward, you will be shown a map of the rest of the floor and may choose how you wish to proceed

607
01:40:05,000 --> 01:40:09,000
Which challenges would you like to face, and which rewards do you want to claim?

608
01:40:10,000 --> 01:40:14,000
Some rooms are more dangerous, afflicting you with debuffs that will persist for the entire Trial

609
01:40:14,000 --> 01:40:22,000
For example, entering this room will afflict you with spiked shell that will cause all monsters in the rest of the Trial to have 50% increased life

610
01:40:23,000 --> 01:40:25,000
You will want to take care if you choose such a path

611
01:40:26,000 --> 01:40:29,000
There are many different challenges and rewards as you journey through the Trial

612
01:40:30,000 --> 01:40:37,000
Deadly traps, waves of monsters, and strange artifacts will test your honor

613
01:40:38,000 --> 01:40:42,000
As you progress, you will be able to gain boons from the Djinn, which will help you on your journey

614
01:40:42,000 --> 01:40:48,000
For example, the Sekhemas Cloak will revive you once if you die, giving you a second shot at a run

615
01:40:49,000 --> 01:40:56,000
One of the rewards you may find is Sacred Water, an extremely valuable and treasured resource to the Djinn and the Marraketh

616
01:40:57,000 --> 01:41:04,000
Trading it with the Djinn will allow you to receive many benefits. You can recover honor, gain additional boons, or remove afflictions

617
01:41:05,000 --> 01:41:10,000
At the end of the floor, you will find a powerful boss which will truly test your limitations

618
01:41:10,000 --> 01:41:13,000
In order to ascend, you will need to defeat him

619
01:41:22,000 --> 01:41:27,000
Having defeated the boss, you've earned the right to ascend, but first, the loot

620
01:41:28,000 --> 01:41:32,000
The keys you have found may be used to open the various treasures in the vault at the end of the floor

621
01:41:33,000 --> 01:41:37,000
We only have a single bronze key, so we'll just have to open one of these small chests

622
01:41:37,000 --> 01:41:40,000
If you want to open the better ones, you'll need silver or gold keys

623
01:41:41,000 --> 01:41:47,000
Let's use the Altar of Ascendancy. Your first ascension will allow you to pick your class and grant you two points to use in the tree

624
01:41:48,000 --> 01:41:54,000
Now there are more floors and many more rewards that can be found within the Trial of the Sekhemas, but we'll save that for the section on the endgame

625
01:41:55,000 --> 01:41:58,000
For now, let's talk about the second Ascendancy Trial, the Trial of Chaos

626
01:41:59,000 --> 01:42:03,000
In Path of Exile 2, you can choose whichever trial you like to earn your ascension

627
01:42:03,000 --> 01:42:06,000
Each culture on Rayclast had their own methods to ascend

628
01:42:07,000 --> 01:42:12,000
If the Trial of the Sekhemas is not your kind of playstyle, or you're finding it too difficult, you could try another

629
01:42:13,000 --> 01:42:16,000
You can gain all your ascension points from just one, or mix and match them. It's up to you

630
01:42:17,000 --> 01:42:21,000
For early access, we will have two trials as options, with a third trial coming later for the full release

631
01:42:23,000 --> 01:42:26,000
While exploring the Vaal jungle, you'll discover the Temple of Chaos

632
01:42:27,000 --> 01:42:31,000
Before the Vaal embraced the science of corruption, their civilization worshipped chaos

633
01:42:31,000 --> 01:42:35,000
This ancient trial was once used by the Vaal to test their high priests

634
01:42:36,000 --> 01:42:39,000
A high priest of the Vaal must show willingness to risk everything to gain power

635
01:42:40,000 --> 01:42:44,000
Entry to the trial requires a token from a strange entity known only as the Trialmaster

636
01:42:45,000 --> 01:42:48,000
For those in which he sees potential, he shall inscribe and ultimate him

637
01:42:49,000 --> 01:42:53,000
Many have attempted these trials in search of greatness, most have perished

638
01:42:54,000 --> 01:42:56,000
Will you be able to defy the odds?

639
01:42:56,000 --> 01:43:00,000
Before you begin each chamber, the Trialmaster will offer you a reward and a choice

640
01:43:01,000 --> 01:43:04,000
Choose one of three tribulations to affect you through the rest of the trial

641
01:43:05,000 --> 01:43:11,000
These modifiers might beef up the monsters, curse the player, or add environmental hazards like turrets or trap runes

642
01:43:12,000 --> 01:43:14,000
In this case, we will be picking Shocking Turrets

643
01:43:18,000 --> 01:43:22,000
As you enter the room, the Trialmaster will fill it with hazards to test your commitment

644
01:43:22,000 --> 01:43:28,000
In this case, you must destroy all the monsters that fill the room, while dealing with the lightning projectiles from the Shocking Turrets

645
01:43:52,000 --> 01:43:55,000
After each room, you will need to make a choice

646
01:43:56,000 --> 01:43:59,000
Take the rewards you have earned so far, or go double or nothing

647
01:44:00,000 --> 01:44:02,000
Increase your rewards, but take on more risk

648
01:44:03,000 --> 01:44:08,000
Each tribulation you add is minor on its own, but they quickly stack on top of each other and can become overwhelming

649
01:44:09,000 --> 01:44:14,000
There are many types of chambers in the trial, each will test your resolve in different ways

650
01:44:15,000 --> 01:44:19,000
This one simply requires you to choose one of the three chambers to test your resolve

651
01:44:19,000 --> 01:44:21,000
Each chamber will test your resolve in different ways

652
01:44:22,000 --> 01:44:24,000
This one simply requires you to survive for a certain amount of time

653
01:44:25,000 --> 01:44:30,000
Another requires you to escort the stone idol through the level as elevators full of monsters descend to attack you

654
01:44:31,000 --> 01:44:35,000
Should you be able to get through the first three chambers, you will face your first boss

655
01:44:36,000 --> 01:44:41,000
The order of the bosses is random, and combined with the tribulations you have selected, the fight will never feel the same

656
01:44:43,000 --> 01:44:45,000
After defeating the boss, you may claim your rewards

657
01:44:45,000 --> 01:44:48,000
Of course there are the items, but you also gain the right to ascend

658
01:44:50,000 --> 01:44:54,000
If you already did the trial of the secondments, then you can claim two more points to add to your ascendancy class

659
01:44:55,000 --> 01:45:02,000
Now it's possible to go much deeper, there are more bosses, rewards and risks to take, but we'll talk more about that when we get to endgame

660
01:45:03,000 --> 01:45:05,000
So how about we talk about that now?

661
01:45:06,000 --> 01:45:12,000
So far we've only been showing you footage from the campaign, but some people would argue that the endgame is where the game truly begins

662
01:45:12,000 --> 01:45:17,000
Something that happens almost every time a new action RPG launches is people saying, there isn't enough endgame content

663
01:45:18,000 --> 01:45:24,000
Well, we want to make sure that in Peewee 2 people don't feel that way, and we actually only changed our development priority for this recently

664
01:45:25,000 --> 01:45:29,000
The first three acts of Peewee 2 already take around 25 hours to complete if you're a new player

665
01:45:30,000 --> 01:45:32,000
This is already a pretty significant campaign

666
01:45:33,000 --> 01:45:36,000
On the other hand, people spend hundreds of hours in endgame each league

667
01:45:36,000 --> 01:45:39,000
We realised that finishing the rest of the campaign for early access was actually a bad idea

668
01:45:40,000 --> 01:45:44,000
Instead of having acts 4-6 in early access, we could concentrate on endgame and make that great

669
01:45:45,000 --> 01:45:49,000
For new players, a 25 hour campaign is already a huge game with lots of content

670
01:45:50,000 --> 01:45:54,000
But for existing action RPG players, what you mostly care about is all the endgame challenges to overcome

671
01:45:55,000 --> 01:45:59,000
So several months ago we switched the entire development team's focus over to making endgame content

672
01:46:00,000 --> 01:46:05,000
At the start of early access there will be 50 bosses and around 100 new characters

673
01:46:06,000 --> 01:46:10,000
And around 400 monster types, but the great thing is that the rest of the game is like 80% there

674
01:46:11,000 --> 01:46:15,000
We'll be adding content to roughly double the size of the game during early access and inter-release

675
01:46:16,000 --> 01:46:20,000
Now in order to make the endgame happen at the same character level as what it would be after we added the rest of the acts

676
01:46:21,000 --> 01:46:26,000
We've added a second difficulty level called Cruel, where you repeat the campaign with all the monsters and bosses levelled up

677
01:46:27,000 --> 01:46:28,000
And of course new rewards

678
01:46:29,000 --> 01:46:31,000
You can kind of think of it as like a new game plus

679
01:46:32,000 --> 01:46:35,000
It's also a lot faster to get through the content the second time as your clear speed increases

680
01:46:36,000 --> 01:46:39,000
That will take you to around level 65 where the endgame begins

681
01:46:40,000 --> 01:46:43,000
Once we add the remaining three acts we'll be removing Cruel difficulty

682
01:46:44,000 --> 01:46:46,000
So you'll progress straight from the Intervax 6 to endgame

683
01:46:47,000 --> 01:46:48,000
But what is the endgame?

684
01:46:49,000 --> 01:46:51,000
To explain that I'll hand over to Mark, he can tell you all about it

685
01:46:53,000 --> 01:46:57,000
Hi, I'm Mark Roberts, game director on Path of Exile 2

686
01:46:58,000 --> 01:47:04,000
Well, one thing that Path of Exile is known for is having a lot of distinct endgame content to choose between

687
01:47:05,000 --> 01:47:14,000
Each endgame mechanic needs to have its own progression system, areas, bosses, rewards and player power that can only be gained from that content

688
01:47:15,000 --> 01:47:22,000
We are going to be adding a lot more over time, but for Path of Exile 2 we decided to start with seven distinct systems you can progress through

689
01:47:23,000 --> 01:47:28,000
This is the Atlas, and it serves as the core of the endgame for Path of Exile 2

690
01:47:29,000 --> 01:47:31,000
It's infinite and expands in all directions

691
01:47:31,000 --> 01:47:38,000
Now we are not going to spoil the plot too much here, but corruption from the beast has blighted the land and your objective is to help fight it

692
01:47:39,000 --> 01:47:45,000
In the center of the Atlas you will find the Ziggurat, a temple in which the Vaal research the fundamentals of space and time

693
01:47:46,000 --> 01:47:51,000
Here we can open portals to nearby locations and begin cleansing corruption and finding resources

694
01:47:52,000 --> 01:47:55,000
In order to power the portal device we will need waystones

695
01:47:56,000 --> 01:48:00,000
Each waystone has a tear which will determine the level of the monsters that you will face

696
01:48:01,000 --> 01:48:06,000
To go to an area simply click one that is adjacent to an area that you have already completed

697
01:48:07,000 --> 01:48:09,000
Insert the waystone and click traverse

698
01:48:10,000 --> 01:48:13,000
Portals will open allowing you and your party to travel to the area you have selected

699
01:48:14,000 --> 01:48:20,000
All the areas in the endgame feel distinct from the locations in the campaign and we have dialled the randomisation up to 11

700
01:48:21,000 --> 01:48:27,000
The monster packs you will face in each map are totally random and the combination of them can lead to some very interesting combat situations

701
01:48:27,000 --> 01:48:33,000
There are over 400 monster types in early access and they have a lot of varied and interesting abilities

702
01:48:34,000 --> 01:48:37,000
Depending on which combinations you face you might find some serious challenges

703
01:48:38,000 --> 01:48:44,000
In order to cleanse the corruption from the area you will need to defeat all the powerful rare and unique enemies in it

704
01:48:45,000 --> 01:48:50,000
Once you have done that the area will be marked as completed and you will be able to travel past it to progress deeper into the world

705
01:48:51,000 --> 01:48:57,000
If you die then the map can no longer be run and you will have to find another way around to get to the areas behind it

706
01:48:58,000 --> 01:49:02,000
There are also all kinds of other random encounters you might run into as you play maps

707
01:49:03,000 --> 01:49:09,000
One such encounter are precursor artefacts. These are ancient, corrupting monuments that irradiate the monsters around them

708
01:49:10,000 --> 01:49:12,000
The monsters that feed off the corruption are drawn to their power

709
01:49:13,000 --> 01:49:16,000
If you defeat the monsters and cleanse the artefact you will get a powerful temporary buff

710
01:49:16,000 --> 01:49:24,000
Some of the buffs make you faster, others rain lightning or fire around you and some even give you increased experience or help you find better items

711
01:49:25,000 --> 01:49:31,000
You can also find strong boxes. These enigmatic chests guard piles of treasure but are always a trap

712
01:49:32,000 --> 01:49:39,000
Monsters lie in wait to attack you the moment you open it and the boxes often have mechanisms to unleash powerful spells or dangerous debuffs

713
01:49:39,000 --> 01:49:47,000
There are different types of strong boxes containing different items and you can even use your currency items to craft them on the fly so you can optimise the content

714
01:49:48,000 --> 01:49:50,000
But be careful of opening one you can't handle

715
01:49:59,000 --> 01:50:04,000
Sometimes you'll discover monsters frozen in essences, solidified crystalline corruption

716
01:50:04,000 --> 01:50:13,000
These dangerous monsters can be broken free. If you defeat them, the essence they drop can be used to upgrade normal items to magic items with a guaranteed mod from a category

717
01:50:15,000 --> 01:50:20,000
For example, we could use this one on some boats to ensure a movement speed mod

718
01:50:23,000 --> 01:50:28,000
Rarely, essences will also drop that allow you to upgrade magics to rares adding the guaranteed mod

719
01:50:34,000 --> 01:50:39,000
This is incredibly powerful since it allows you to get a second deterministic mod in your crafting projects

720
01:50:40,000 --> 01:50:47,000
Combining these with the currencies that are commonly found at Rayclast for modifying items and we can get a very nice pair of boots indeed

721
01:50:49,000 --> 01:50:54,000
Waitstones, like all items, can also be crafted using your currency items

722
01:50:56,000 --> 01:51:01,000
Adding prefix mods will improve the rewards while suffix mods will make it easier to craft items

723
01:51:01,000 --> 01:51:05,000
The more dangerous a map is, the more waystones will drop

724
01:51:06,000 --> 01:51:13,000
Adding mods to your waystones is key to progressing to higher tiers and sustaining them, but it will require you to take on larger challenges

725
01:51:14,000 --> 01:51:18,000
There are a variety of factors you have to consider when crafting your waystones

726
01:51:19,000 --> 01:51:26,000
Some maps will have higher density, some lower, some have more magic and rare chests, more monsters, some are more linear and others more open

727
01:51:26,000 --> 01:51:31,000
Make sure you explore and think about what makes certain maps good if you want to maximise your returns

728
01:51:32,000 --> 01:51:38,000
As you cleanse corruption from higher and higher tiers of the atlas, you will gain points that you can spend in the atlas tree

729
01:51:39,000 --> 01:51:43,000
This tree allows you to juice the danger and rewards of all areas in the endgame

730
01:51:44,000 --> 01:51:51,000
You could increase the number of monsters, the number of rares, the number of precursor artifacts or strongboxes, even the quantity of items you can get

731
01:51:51,000 --> 01:51:58,000
As you explore the endgame world map, you will notice various different biomes, from snowcapped mountains to dense jungle valleys

732
01:51:59,000 --> 01:52:01,000
Most maps are restricted to certain biomes

733
01:52:02,000 --> 01:52:06,000
As you continue to explore deeper into the atlas, there are all sorts of things to discover

734
01:52:07,000 --> 01:52:12,000
These cities are constructed by different peoples of Rayclust and have specific items that can be found there

735
01:52:13,000 --> 01:52:18,000
These strange structures marked on the map don't appear to be the same as the other maps you have seen

736
01:52:18,000 --> 01:52:24,000
These strange structures marked on the map don't appear to do anything for now, perhaps you'll work out how to use them later

737
01:52:25,000 --> 01:52:32,000
You might find unique maps like Untainted Paradise, an undisturbed island full of beasts that give an extreme amount of experience

738
01:52:33,000 --> 01:52:37,000
You may even find a lonely man just enjoying his retirement who will give you a unique item for free

739
01:52:38,000 --> 01:52:42,000
In addition, you can find special areas that would make a good spot to set up camp

740
01:52:43,000 --> 01:52:47,000
Clear these areas off their hostile inhabitants and you'll be able to claim them as your own hideout

741
01:52:48,000 --> 01:52:55,000
You can decorate your hideout as you see fit and invite various NPCs to join you there to create your own personal base of operations

742
01:52:56,000 --> 01:52:59,000
A great tool for exploration are towers

743
01:53:00,000 --> 01:53:03,000
These mysterious precursor constructs are dotted around the atlas

744
01:53:04,000 --> 01:53:08,000
Completing the tower will reveal a large area around it, allowing you to scout out your next challenge

745
01:53:09,000 --> 01:53:12,000
There are lots of things to find, so keep looking

746
01:53:13,000 --> 01:53:15,000
Some sections of your atlas are influenced by corruption

747
01:53:15,000 --> 01:53:20,000
This adds extra modifiers to the maps in the region, increasing difficulty and rewards

748
01:53:21,000 --> 01:53:30,000
Here, slaying monsters in close proximity to each other will cause the vestiges of corruption within them to merge together, forming powerful and grotesque abominations

749
01:53:31,000 --> 01:53:35,000
You may have noticed while looking at the atlas that some of the areas have these icons above them

750
01:53:36,000 --> 01:53:39,000
The icon indicates that the area contains some kind of special encounter

751
01:53:40,000 --> 01:53:43,000
This icon indicates that the area has a powerful boss

752
01:53:43,000 --> 01:53:49,000
Because only 1 in 4 maps contain a map boss, we are able to make them very powerful and very rewarding

753
01:53:50,000 --> 01:53:56,000
These bosses come from the campaign, but have had their difficulty increased with changes to AI and some of their abilities

754
01:53:57,000 --> 01:54:01,000
It's worth noting that because you can see where the bosses are, you can choose to take them on or avoid them

755
01:54:02,000 --> 01:54:08,000
If you do choose to hunt bosses though, then you will be rewarded with special points for the boss hunting section of the Atlas skill tree

756
01:54:08,000 --> 01:54:13,000
The points here will allow you to specialise in boss killing, giving you much greater rewards for defeating them

757
01:54:16,000 --> 01:54:25,000
For each different type of content in the endgame, we are adding specialised trees in order to make it so you don't feel the need to re-spec your points when you change between different types of content

758
01:54:26,000 --> 01:54:30,000
We will be showing you 7 of these by the end of this presentation, so there is still a lot more to come

759
01:54:31,000 --> 01:54:36,000
Bosses are not the only icon you will see on the Atlas, let's take a look at one of the endgame systems, Breach

760
01:54:37,000 --> 01:54:40,000
If you played PoE 1, you might be familiar with Breach

761
01:54:41,000 --> 01:54:44,000
For PoE 2 we have created sequels to several PoE 1 leagues

762
01:54:45,000 --> 01:54:50,000
While the mechanic is familiar, the monsters, bosses, rewards and progression are all new

763
01:54:51,000 --> 01:54:59,000
A breach is a tear in the fabric of reality, opening it will allow you to see the demons and otherworldly monstrosities that lie in wait on this other plane of existence

764
01:55:00,000 --> 01:55:03,000
By engaging with a breach, you will create a bridge between their world and Rayclast

765
01:55:03,000 --> 01:55:07,000
In order to keep the breach open, you will need to kill the demons that pour forth

766
01:55:08,000 --> 01:55:12,000
The faster you can kill the monsters, the more monsters you will fight and the more loot you will find

767
01:55:13,000 --> 01:55:17,000
You can also find clasped hands that will open and drop more items if you run over them

768
01:55:18,000 --> 01:55:21,000
These can be a good boost to the rewards of the breach, so keep an eye out

769
01:55:23,000 --> 01:55:27,000
One of the rewards that you may find while fighting monsters from Breach are tablets

770
01:55:27,000 --> 01:55:32,000
Tablets are special items that can be used with precursor towers to add more encounters to the Atlas

771
01:55:33,000 --> 01:55:35,000
Breaches will drop Breach tablets

772
01:55:36,000 --> 01:55:41,000
Clicking on a completed tower will allow you to consume the tablet to add more breaches to areas within range of the tower

773
01:55:42,000 --> 01:55:44,000
This makes all the content in the Atlas self-sustaining

774
01:55:45,000 --> 01:55:50,000
Want to do more breaches? Find the tablets, add them to your towers, get more breaches, getting more tablets

775
01:55:51,000 --> 01:55:53,000
Soon your Atlas will be covered in otherworldly domains

776
01:55:53,000 --> 01:55:55,000
In addition, like all items in PoE, you can craft them

777
01:55:56,000 --> 01:56:00,000
Use your currency to add mods to your tablets, allowing you to upgrade all the breaches in range

778
01:56:01,000 --> 01:56:02,000
Tablets can have up to two mods

779
01:56:03,000 --> 01:56:11,000
These mods do things like adding extra rare monsters, extra clasped hands, or even mods to density of breaches, allowing you to keep them open longer

780
01:56:12,000 --> 01:56:15,000
Often you will find multiple towers near to each other with overlapping areas of effect

781
01:56:16,000 --> 01:56:20,000
This can allow you to rarely juice the mechanic by stacking them up to the top of the tower

782
01:56:20,000 --> 01:56:24,000
This can allow you to rarely juice the mechanic by stacking the mods from multiple tablets

783
01:56:25,000 --> 01:56:30,000
In your fight to hold the Breach demons at bay, you may want to use the powers of their world against them

784
01:56:31,000 --> 01:56:36,000
Each end game mechanic always has player power that can only be gained from that mechanic, and Breach is no different

785
01:56:37,000 --> 01:56:44,000
In Breach you will find catalysts, items that can increase the quality of rings and amulets by improving specific mods

786
01:56:44,000 --> 01:56:50,000
You can also find Breach Rings, a special base type that can have its quality improved by catalysts up to 50%

787
01:56:51,000 --> 01:56:53,000
In this case you could create a ring with around 170 life

788
01:56:54,000 --> 01:56:59,000
Breach rings can become some of the strongest rings in the game, giving you some good motivation to face the demon hordes

789
01:57:00,000 --> 01:57:04,000
In addition, each end game mechanic needs to have a pinnacle end game encounter

790
01:57:05,000 --> 01:57:07,000
While killing Breach monsters you may find Breach Splinters

791
01:57:08,000 --> 01:57:10,000
Collect enough of these and you'll be able to create a Breach Stone

792
01:57:10,000 --> 01:57:17,000
Using a Vaal technology called the Realm Gate, you can use your Breach Stone to access their domain and bring the fight to them

793
01:57:18,000 --> 01:57:22,000
In this twisted domain you will find nothing but a single massive Breach

794
01:57:23,000 --> 01:57:26,000
Triggering it will reveal hordes of Breach inhabitants

795
01:57:26,000 --> 01:57:30,000
And should you be fast enough, you will be able to fight their leader, Zest, We That Are One

796
01:57:56,000 --> 01:58:03,000
This is just one of the pinnacle encounters of POE 2

797
01:58:04,000 --> 01:58:07,000
We won't be showing the rest of them, so you will have to discover them for yourself

798
01:58:08,000 --> 01:58:11,000
But rest assured, this is some of the hardest content we have ever made

799
01:58:12,000 --> 01:58:16,000
All of these encounters have spent a lot of time and effort to create a pinnacle encounter

800
01:58:17,000 --> 01:58:19,000
And we hope you enjoyed it

801
01:58:19,000 --> 01:58:20,000
We will be showing the rest of them, so you will have to discover them for yourself

802
01:58:21,000 --> 01:58:24,000
But rest assured, this is some of the hardest content we have ever made

803
01:58:25,000 --> 01:58:28,000
All of these encounters have specific uniques that can only be found from them

804
01:58:29,000 --> 01:58:32,000
But that's not all, we still have the progression system

805
01:58:33,000 --> 01:58:37,000
Defeating Zest will give you points to allocate into the Breach section of the Atlas Tree

806
01:58:38,000 --> 01:58:43,000
Allocating these points will make Breaches and the Breach domain even harder, but will give you more rewards

807
01:58:43,000 --> 01:58:49,000
The small nodes will increase the difficulty of the Twisted Domain, while the large nodes have more specific bonuses

808
01:58:50,000 --> 01:58:55,000
For example, this node adds more Clasped Hands to your Breaches, and adds a pack of magic monsters that can guard them

809
01:58:56,000 --> 01:59:02,000
Get some more points and you can allocate Waking Nightmare, which will double the number of splinters you get from Clasped Hands

810
01:59:03,000 --> 01:59:05,000
And inflict you with a mysterious debuff

811
01:59:06,000 --> 01:59:09,000
In order to earn more points you will need to defeat Zest at a higher difficulty

812
01:59:09,000 --> 01:59:15,000
And some rewards from Zest can only be found by increasing the difficulty of the Twisted Domain above certain thresholds

813
01:59:16,000 --> 01:59:21,000
Defeating Zest at difficulty 4 will be a challenge indeed, but there are many more threats in Rayclass

814
01:59:23,000 --> 01:59:28,000
Ritual Altars are sacrificial sites, built by the mysterious King in the Mists

815
01:59:29,000 --> 01:59:34,000
If you encounter this symbol on the Atlas, then you know that the area contains Ritual Altars

816
01:59:35,000 --> 01:59:36,000
Ritual Altars demand tribute

817
01:59:36,000 --> 01:59:40,000
Every monster you slaughter in the circle will feed the altar

818
01:59:41,000 --> 01:59:43,000
After the sacrifice, touch it to begin the ritual

819
01:59:44,000 --> 01:59:50,000
The monsters you just killed will be resurrected by the King of the Mists' dark magic, and you must fight to survive

820
01:59:53,000 --> 01:59:58,000
The tribute you have offered to the altar can be spent to buy powerful items, but they can be expensive

821
01:59:59,000 --> 02:00:01,000
To gain more tribute you will want to find more altars

822
02:00:01,000 --> 02:00:09,000
Each successive ritual you do within an area will spawn the monsters revived by the previous ones, in addition to the ones you sacrifice next to it

823
02:00:10,000 --> 02:00:16,000
By the end of an area you will be fighting a truly imposing number of foes, but will have a significant amount of tribute to spend

824
02:00:17,000 --> 02:00:19,000
One of the rewards you can buy with tribute are Omens

825
02:00:20,000 --> 02:00:22,000
These are special items that allow for meta-crafting

826
02:00:23,000 --> 02:00:25,000
Crafting items that affect other crafting items

827
02:00:25,000 --> 02:00:27,000
Have an item with good prefixes but bad suffixes?

828
02:00:28,000 --> 02:00:31,000
This omen will help you to remove the mods you don't want while keeping the ones you do

829
02:00:32,000 --> 02:00:35,000
There are a bunch more of these with different effects, but we will leave them for you to discover

830
02:00:36,000 --> 02:00:41,000
Now don't forget that Ritual will also drop tablets, which can be used to specialize into getting more rituals

831
02:00:42,000 --> 02:00:46,000
If you want to get to the Pinnacle boss of Ritual, then you will probably want to use them

832
02:00:47,000 --> 02:00:50,000
They can also be crafted to grant mods, making your rituals more rewarding

833
02:00:51,000 --> 02:00:53,000
The Pinnacle encounter of Ritual is the King in the Mists

834
02:00:53,000 --> 02:00:58,000
Feared by the Asmiri people, he is said to have brought eternal darkness to the Wildwood

835
02:00:59,000 --> 02:01:04,000
We won't show the encounter, but just like Breach, there are a range of unique items you can get for defeating him

836
02:01:05,000 --> 02:01:07,000
And you will gain points in the Ritual section of the Atlas Tree

837
02:01:08,000 --> 02:01:11,000
Some maps have been touched by insanity

838
02:01:12,000 --> 02:01:14,000
A mysterious entity has taken a special interest in you

839
02:01:15,000 --> 02:01:18,000
Step through the Looking Glass and you will find your nightmares coming to life

840
02:01:18,000 --> 02:01:23,000
When you touch a mirror, the mists of Delirium will spread out across the area, infecting your mind

841
02:01:24,000 --> 02:01:29,000
You must stay within the mist to maintain the nightmare, which is as profitable as it is terrifying

842
02:01:30,000 --> 02:01:32,000
Everything you kill will increase the rewards that drop

843
02:01:33,000 --> 02:01:36,000
However, the deeper into the mist you travel, the stronger the monsters are

844
02:01:37,000 --> 02:01:38,000
Be careful not to overstay your welcome

845
02:01:39,000 --> 02:01:42,000
Rare and unique enemies will become vessels for terrifying demons

846
02:01:43,000 --> 02:01:46,000
Who will manifest out of them to unleash powerful attacks on you

847
02:01:46,000 --> 02:01:50,000
The mist also offers a strange crafting material, Distilled Emotions

848
02:01:51,000 --> 02:01:56,000
By combining these emotions you are able to instill your amulet with a notable from the passive skill tree

849
02:01:57,000 --> 02:02:00,000
This is like gaining an extra passive point for free attached to your gear

850
02:02:01,000 --> 02:02:04,000
They are also particularly great because you don't have to traverse the tree to get them

851
02:02:05,000 --> 02:02:08,000
Allowing you to get off-class bonuses that would normally be much harder to get

852
02:02:09,000 --> 02:02:13,000
Distilled Emotions can also be used to instill your endgame maps

853
02:02:14,000 --> 02:02:17,000
Applying Delirious to them and adding additional difficulty and rewards

854
02:02:18,000 --> 02:02:20,000
Allowing you to further juice your endgame maps

855
02:02:21,000 --> 02:02:23,000
The tablets you can find from Delirium can be used to further improve it

856
02:02:24,000 --> 02:02:30,000
Increase pack size, make the fog dissipate slower, or improve your progress towards the pinnacle encounter of Delirium

857
02:02:31,000 --> 02:02:34,000
Speaking of which, every now and then you will find Simulacrum Splinters

858
02:02:34,000 --> 02:02:39,000
The mysterious entity will create strange encounters based on warped versions of your own memories

859
02:02:40,000 --> 02:02:44,000
Monsters and Simulacrums come in waves that get progressively more difficult

860
02:02:45,000 --> 02:02:49,000
You will receive loot at the end of each wave and you will have to make the decision to leave now or continue on

861
02:02:50,000 --> 02:02:52,000
Facing up against even tougher foes from the mist

862
02:02:53,000 --> 02:02:57,000
The bosses you will face as you get deeper into a Simulacrum are truly terrifying

863
02:02:57,000 --> 02:03:03,000
If you can complete a Simulacrum, you will gain points for the Delirium section of the Atlas Skill Tree

864
02:03:05,000 --> 02:03:07,000
Next up we have Expedition

865
02:03:08,000 --> 02:03:13,000
Occasionally while clearing Corruption, you will encounter these Kal-Gurren settlers

866
02:03:14,000 --> 02:03:18,000
The Kal-Gurrens have discovered ancient burial sites with lost Verisium artifacts

867
02:03:19,000 --> 02:03:21,000
And they want you to help dig them up with explosives

868
02:03:22,000 --> 02:03:25,000
The Kal-Gurrens have marked the locations where the relics can be found

869
02:03:25,000 --> 02:03:28,000
Place explosives as best you can to dig up as many as possible

870
02:03:29,000 --> 02:03:30,000
There is just one problem

871
02:03:31,000 --> 02:03:33,000
Corruption has brought the corpses of their ancestors to life

872
02:03:34,000 --> 02:03:37,000
So you might have to do a little clean up before you can reclaim the artifacts

873
02:03:43,000 --> 02:03:44,000
You can also find Remnants

874
02:03:45,000 --> 02:03:48,000
The destruction of which will further anger the restless dead

875
02:03:49,000 --> 02:03:53,000
Each one you blow up will make the subsequent monsters more powerful but also more rewarding

876
02:03:55,000 --> 02:04:01,000
Danug, Rog, Tujun and Gwennan will exchange the artifacts for useful items and runic magic

877
02:04:02,000 --> 02:04:06,000
You can also find tablets to increase the number of expeditions and the rewards

878
02:04:07,000 --> 02:04:09,000
This one increases the radius of explosives

879
02:04:10,000 --> 02:04:12,000
While this one increases the number of remnants you will find

880
02:04:14,000 --> 02:04:16,000
Eventually you might discover a Logbook

881
02:04:17,000 --> 02:04:19,000
These are special maps full of buried treasure and relics

882
02:04:20,000 --> 02:04:22,000
Essentially one giant dig site

883
02:04:23,000 --> 02:04:29,000
