884
02:04:30,000 --> 02:04:31,000
But be careful

885
02:04:32,000 --> 02:04:33,000
Many remnants have mods that can really break your build

886
02:04:34,000 --> 02:04:36,000
So you will probably want to avoid these ones

887
02:04:37,000 --> 02:04:40,000
If you add too many remnants you could easily make the encounter harder than you can handle

888
02:04:41,000 --> 02:04:43,000
There are all sorts of interesting things buried under the ground in Logbooks

889
02:04:44,000 --> 02:04:47,000
You might find dripping caves and hidden pirate caches

890
02:04:47,000 --> 02:04:52,000
But the most powerful encounter is Olroth, the ancient undead commander of the Knights of the Sun

891
02:04:53,000 --> 02:04:59,000
Defeating him will grant you unique rewards as well as points to spend in the expedition section of the Atlas tree

892
02:05:00,000 --> 02:05:03,000
So those are the endgame systems on the Atlas but we are not done yet

893
02:05:04,000 --> 02:05:07,000
The trials we talked about earlier have much more content when you get to endgame 2

894
02:05:08,000 --> 02:05:15,000
Just like the other endgame systems, they also have progression mechanics, unique rewards and player power that can only be gained from them

895
02:05:16,000 --> 02:05:21,000
As you get higher level coins for the trial of the Sekimas, you will unlock more floors to explore

896
02:05:23,000 --> 02:05:27,000
Each floor has its own challenging brooms and a floor boss that you will need to kill

897
02:05:33,000 --> 02:05:40,000
There are four floors in total, leading to another pinnacle boss at the end of the last floor which can only be accessed at endgame

898
02:05:40,000 --> 02:05:45,000
The trial of the Sekimas is where you'll find jewels, which you can socket into your tree

899
02:05:46,000 --> 02:05:48,000
These are like passives that you can craft with your currency items

900
02:05:49,000 --> 02:05:54,000
They can be really powerful as they allow you to stack modifiers that may not be easily accessible on the tree normally

901
02:05:55,000 --> 02:05:57,000
This jewel gives lightning damage and shock chance for example

902
02:05:58,000 --> 02:06:02,000
There are quite a few jewel sockets on the tree so it's possible to gain a lot of power here

903
02:06:03,000 --> 02:06:09,000
There are also other types of jewels that don't provide any bonuses themselves but affect other passives surrounding them

904
02:06:10,000 --> 02:06:13,000
This jewel increases the effect of small nodes and radius by 25%

905
02:06:14,000 --> 02:06:18,000
With careful placement in the tree, you could get a significant amount of power from it

906
02:06:19,000 --> 02:06:24,000
There are also unique jewels available with very interesting effects, but you will have to find those for yourself

907
02:06:25,000 --> 02:06:32,000
In order to push further into the trial and uncover the secrets of the Marakev, you will want to take advantage of its progression system, relics

908
02:06:33,000 --> 02:06:37,000
Relics are items that can be placed in the relic altar as you start the trial

909
02:06:37,000 --> 02:06:42,000
They give special bonuses that affect the trial, making it easier and increasing its rewards

910
02:06:43,000 --> 02:06:46,000
Of course, you can craft these with your currency items, making them even stronger

911
02:06:47,000 --> 02:06:54,000
If you can complete the entire trial overcoming all four floors, the final boss will reward you with one of many unique relics

912
02:06:55,000 --> 02:07:00,000
These relics will be consumed when used on your next run, but can reward you with unique and powerful items

913
02:07:01,000 --> 02:07:03,000
For example, this is the Last Flame

914
02:07:03,000 --> 02:07:09,000
If you use it, you will have only one honor for the entire trial, so you will need to do a completely hitless run

915
02:07:12,000 --> 02:07:15,000
The Trial of Chaos also extends into the endgame

916
02:07:16,000 --> 02:07:21,000
As you gain inscribed ultimatums of higher and higher levels, the number of chambers that you can go through increases

917
02:07:22,000 --> 02:07:26,000
In true Vaal style, this allows you to take even more risks for even more rewards

918
02:07:27,000 --> 02:07:31,000
At endgame, you can progress through up to 10 chambers with 3 bosses on a single run

919
02:07:31,000 --> 02:07:36,000
Stacking 10 tribulations on top of each other will make this a significant challenge, but it's worth it

920
02:07:37,000 --> 02:07:41,000
The Trialmaster will tempt you with items of the Vaal empire, such as Vaal Orbs

921
02:07:42,000 --> 02:07:46,000
Vaal Orbs are powerful crafting items that corrupt your gear with random mysterious outcomes

922
02:07:47,000 --> 02:07:54,000
Corruption prevents an item from being modified further, so it has to be the last step of your craft, but it's also the most impactful one

923
02:07:54,000 --> 02:08:02,000
For example, if you use one on your body armor, it might add a new powerful enchantment, or it might reroll up to half of its modifiers

924
02:08:03,000 --> 02:08:10,000
Vaal Orbs also have the ability to add a socket, allowing you to bypass the normal restriction of how many sockets an item can have

925
02:08:11,000 --> 02:08:15,000
A body armor could get up to 3 sockets this way, allowing for a significant number of mods

926
02:08:16,000 --> 02:08:18,000
Vaal Orbs can even modify uniques

927
02:08:18,000 --> 02:08:25,000
Adding enchantments or sockets to uniques can make them incredibly powerful, but there is a good chance that you will break them as well

928
02:08:26,000 --> 02:08:29,000
The Trialmaster will also occasionally offer you Soul Cores

929
02:08:30,000 --> 02:08:38,000
Originally formed by Chaos, the Vaal sought to replicate Soul Cores through human sacrifice rituals and blood magic to power their civilization

930
02:08:39,000 --> 02:08:44,000
Soul Cores are powerful socketable items, with mods that cannot be obtained from regular runes

931
02:08:45,000 --> 02:08:49,000
Like all endgame content, there is of course a pinnacle boss

932
02:08:50,000 --> 02:08:52,000
